President Obama hosted the White House Science Fair to celebrate the winners of various science, technology, engineering, and math (STEM) competitions. The fair is part of the President's Educate to Innovate campaign, which aims to improve science and math achievement among American students. The President viewed exhibits of winning student projects and delivered remarks congratulating the students on their achievements. He also announced his appearance on an upcoming episode of Discovery Channel's MythBusters. In addition, the Administration and leading companies are taking further steps to advance STEM education, including placing 3D printers in schools and making design tools freely available to students. The article also provides background information on the importance of STEM education and highlights some of the winning projects showcased at the fair.